@Pranavchiku If you could write a reproducer for the `ELSE IF` thing I'll fix it right away. For the `EQUIVALENCE` error there is another issue #692

```
      SUBROUTINE cdft(which,p,q,t,df,status,bound)
  170 IF (.NOT. (which.EQ.1)) qporq = p .LE. q
      ELSE IF ((2).EQ. (which)) THEN
  310 END IF
      RETURN
      END
```
This produces the same error @konradha

Your example does not compile with gfortran and I'm trying to figure out what's the issue for this involved nesting.

Edit: found it, will hopefully find a nice fix then. Thanks @Pranavchiku 

Edit2: please check back after #695 has been merged into main

Also @Pranavchiku @Smit-create -- `tokenizer error: Expecting terminating symbol for subroutine` is not a single issue class, please see if you can find out what's the underlying issue we have to tackle. Thanks :)
Apart from the example containing "include", these parse just fine.
See #777 for include. So I am going to close this issue as fixed.
